  "body": "Version: V0.11.0-rc.2\r\nOS: Ubuntu 22.10\r\n\r\nCommunity/Edit Community/under the ‘Tags’ header, the tags field should have a grey fill and grey hint text.\r\n\r\nThe ‘Community Tags’ dialog that opens when a user clicks the tags field is broken.   \r\n\r\n***\r\n\r\n##Scenario 1\r\n\r\nPrecondition: User is the owner of a community that has no tags.\r\n\r\n<ins>Steps to reproduce:</ins>\r\n\r\n1. In a community that the user is an owner of, navigate to the ‘Edit Community’ screen.\r\n\r\n2. In the ‘Edit Community screen’ scroll down to the ‘Tags’ header. \r\n\r\n<ins>What currently incorrectly happens:</ins>\r\n\r\n3. The filed under the ‘Tags’ header is missing a grey fill and the grey hint text. \r\n\r\n![03 26 incorrect tags button](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/124154641/230024477-c262b694-5f8b-43f8-8543-ff173e84b923.png)\r\n\r\n<ins>What is supposed to happen:</ins>\r\n\r\n3. When a community has no tags, the field under the ‘Tags’ header should have a grey fill and grey hint text as per the screenshot below. \r\n\r\n![03 26 correct tags button](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/124154641/230024603-18396d4f-1930-4dcf-a535-1821e667aad2.png)\r\n\r\n<ins>Other information</ins>\r\n\r\nIf a user opens the ‘Community Tags’ dialog from the ‘Edit Community’ screen and clicks ‘Confirm Community Tags’ with no tags selected, and when the “Changes detected | Cancel | Save changes” popover is displayed, the tags field is correctly displayed with a grey background and grey hint text.  However as soon as the user clicks “Save changes” (or “Cancel”), the Tags field loses it’s grey background and grey hint text.\r\n\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/124154641/230028745-a11d36bf-6214-40cb-8e00-9e77a9ec4544.mp4\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n##Scenario 2\r\n\r\n<ins>Steps to reproduce:</ins>\r\n1. In a community that the user is an owner of, navigate to the ‘Edit Community’ screen.\r\n\r\n2. In the ‘Edit Community screen’ navigate down to the ‘Tags’ header. \r\n\r\n3. Under the ‘Tags’ header, click inside the tags field to open the ‘Community Tags’ selector. \r\n\r\n<ins>What currently incorrectly happens:</ins>\r\n\r\n4. The ‘Community Tags’ selector dialog is broken, see screenshot below.\r\n\r\n![03 26 broken Community Tags dialog](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/124154641/230026016-868a721a-b0cf-42bc-88bf-892b844e04f5.png)\r\n\r\n<ins>What is supposed to happen:</ins>\r\n\r\n4. The ‘Community Tags’  selector dialog should be similar to the ‘Community Tags’ selector dialog in ‘Create New Community’ flow. The only difference is the Edit Community/Community Tags selector dialog should not have the back button in the bottom left corner of the dialog as the user is not being taken back to the previous screen *inside* a dialog window (unlike in the Create New community/Community Tags dialog). \r\n\r\n![03 26 correct community tags dialog](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/124154641/230026151-ce01fc61-4d99-46a1-bc3e-41634c90eb08.png)\r\n\r\nLink to Create New community/Community Tags dialog design in Figma - https://www.figma.com/file/17fc13UBFvInrLgNUKJJg5/Kuba%E2%8E%9CDesktop?node-id=15721-465146&t=ROTse7xDBYt3iJfy-0 \r\n\r\n<ins>Other information</ins>\r\nWhen writing this bug I noticed there is also a regression in the ‘Create New Community’/’Community Tags’ selector dialog in V0.11.0-rc.2 - the tags are not showing. The 'Create New Community’/’Community Tags’ selector dialog works in Windows / V0.10.\r\n\r\n\r\nhttps://user-images.githubusercontent.com/124154641/230026387-277b05b4-321b-48bb-b38d-884a114d5496.mp4\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n",
